  "content": {
    "bodyModel": {
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_0",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b005",
          "text": "Personal Failure in the System We Can’t See",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "H3"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_1",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f542",
          "text": "We are embedded in tapestries of systems that are difficult to see.",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*2BKtvmKj0RJr6m53o0Qyww.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "0593",
          "text": "Right now, the majority of people in the world are living in a rigged economic system that is largely invisible to us. This is why we repeatedly have the experience of trying really hard to “do the right things” but find out that no matter how hard we try, things just aren’t working out for us.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 85,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 63,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ed5a",
          "text": "Our economic systems have become so rigged that only a tiny slice of every society is able to win — at the expense of scarcity wrought onto everyone else. This is why 62 people have the same wealth as 3.7 billion. It is why political outcomes are secured with donations instead of voter turnout. It’s why so many of us are strapped with debts we cannot repay while the billionaire class gets more yachts, more mansions, and more access to wealth with each passing year.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 212,
              "href": "https://www.oxfam.org/en/pressroom/pressreleases/2016-01-18/62-people-own-same-half-world-reveals-oxfam-davos-report",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 167,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 269,
              "href": "http://billmoyers.com/2014/08/14/a-study-in-plutocracy-rich-americans-wield-political-influence-the-rest-of-us-dont/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 224,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 358,
              "href": "http://www.marketwatch.com/story/americas-growing-student-loan-debt-crisis-2016-01-15",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 323,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "efbc",
          "text": "These are designed outcomes. The economy is working exactly how it was set up to function. It isn’t “broken” so much as “fixed” to serve financial elites at the expense of everyone else. An invisible system — which I call the Global Architecture of Wealth Extraction — is functioning behind the scenes to make all of this happen.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 266,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/the-global-architecture-of-wealth-extraction-4c0a6b954a14#.2bfyfya4o",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 226,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 329,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 187,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 27,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 10,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b923",
          "text": "We are taught to take it personally when we fail. If something went wrong, it must be MY fault. I didn’t try hard enough. I wasn’t smart or clever enough. I didn’t want it bad enough. These are the lies we use to imprison ourselves in the monopoly game board set up to extract and hoard wealth all around us. None of us is alone. Everything is connected. Yet when we focus on the individual actions of single actors (ourselves included), the systems that do the work of wealth extraction remain invisible to us. They hide in the unconscious parts of our minds.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 353,
              "href": "http://www.kosmosjournal.org/news/what-if-its-all-connected-humanity-and-the-global-crisis/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 330,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 559,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/systems-of-wealth-hoarding-hide-in-your-mind-bc5998934931#.8qki0iv8a",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 516,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "0a6f",
          "text": "How are we supposed to feel in a world like this? Guilty. Ashamed. Blame ourselves. That is what they want, the people who benefit from the status quo that keeps our foot on the consumption accelerator as we drive our civilization off the cliff of global-warming-overshoot — increasing wealth inequality and societal instability along the way. It is how we become complicit in preserving and perpetuating a system that actively harms us (and most other living things) in order to convert the world’s wealth into numbers on digital spreadsheets for the super-rich.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 101,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 97,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "bf83",
          "text": "Of course, this system may even be invisible to the beneficiaries. As I noted elsewhere, we should not aspire to be like the billionaires among us. They too are psychically damaged by this morally bankrupt economic system. But none of us will get to the heart of the problem if we don’t begin to practice seeing the life-destructive system for what it is.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 87,
              "href": "https://medium.com/swlh/billionaires-are-sick-too-they-need-healing-6ef8a5440f95#.rafar7pws",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 72,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 355,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 305,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5d68",
          "text": "How can we begin to see that which has been made invisible (intentionally through corporate spin in the media and inadvertently by the basic fact that it is dispersed and decentralized across cultures)? The answer is to look for the logic of wealth extraction, see it as a way of thinking or mode of being that endlessly takes without properly giving in return.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 259,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 220,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e799",
          "text": "We can see it in the tax havens and shell companies that hoard away trillions of dollars from governments around the world.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 123,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "dd0e",
          "text": "It shows itself through the misinformation campaigns about “trickle down” theories telling us the best way for prosperity to spread is by giving all the money to already-rich people.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 182,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3f7a",
          "text": "We observe it in the selling of products to fill voids in our souls, where only authentic life experience and human connection is able to make us whole.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 152,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4016",
          "text": "It rears its head in the failure to measure inherent value in the homemaking of mothers or the workings of natural ecosystems that are treated as empty resources to be exploited for financial gain.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 197,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fa8b",
          "text": "We note it in the use of economic measures like “Gross Domestic Product” that rise in number the same way whether disaster strikes, bombs are dropped, or productive exchanges of goods and services leave a money trail.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 217,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fa13",
          "text": "In other words, the system is invisible not because anyone actively hides it. Rather it is invisible because it is a pattern of culture revealed only by studying human thought and behavior. These things only become real because we act them out — in a perverse role-play game of conquest, domination, and spoiling of the Earth.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 188,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 117,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c59c",
          "text": "The system is invisible because it is inside of us. We dream it into being. And herein lies the path to hope.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c702",
          "text": "If we created this Frankenstein monster in our minds (even if it was architected by a few masterminds along the way), we have the power to change it simply by seeing it for what it is and collectively choosing to live a different way.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 68,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 65,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "9d84",
          "text": "Dismantling a system of wealth extraction will take time and effort. Replacing it with a life-affirming economy that promotes individual and community well-being is a process of many hands doing many things for years to come all around the globe.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "6e09",
          "text": "But the first step is to see it for what it is.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4bac",
          "text": "Then, slowly, we awaken to our role as dreamers in the cultural myth. We begin to see ourselves as active creators of the old — therefore offering the possibility that we can choose instead to be active creators of the new.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "071e",
          "text": "Onward, fellow humans.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "bc15023971d0_21",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b515",
          "text": "Want to support my work? Appreciate my writings? Make a contribution here.",
